# Auditing with List Resources

Terraform [list resources](https://developer.hashicorp.com/terraform/language/import/bulk) let you
query your deSEC account to discover and inspect existing infrastructure using `terraform query`.

~> **Note:** List resources require Terraform v1.12 or newer.

## Auditing Domains

Use the `desec_domain` list resource to enumerate all DNS zones in your account:

```terraform
list "desec_domain" "all" {
  provider = desec
}
```

Run the query:

```shell
terraform query
```

Terraform prints each domain's identity (its name). To include full details like DNSSEC keys
and minimum TTL, set `include_resource = true`:

```terraform
list "desec_domain" "all" {
  provider         = desec
  include_resource = true
}
```

You can also find which domain owns a specific fully-qualified domain name using the
`owns_qname` filter:

```terraform
list "desec_domain" "owns" {
  provider = desec
  config {
    owns_qname = "sub.example.com."
  }
}
```

